<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fire in alkaline pool systems is not well understood historically. Although the likelihood of frequent fire is high in most cismontane grasslands of the state, the lower fuel volumes and the wetter condition of the plants in vernal pools with respect to surrounding grasslands may minimize fire spread in vernal pools (Wills 2006). Late summer to fall season fire is likely to have largely neutral to positive effects on the native, seed-banking annuals and geophytes.</div>
